{"commentv2": 1, "number": 8, "id": 2556969, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Bubbles557", "body": "So Xe'ra basically tried to rape Illidan where the light don't shine and everyone got pissed that Illidan defended himself.", "date": "2018-03-09T16:39:08-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Xe'ra tried an intervention and rehab for our blind magic junkie Illidan, but turns out Illidan would rather kill than go without his fix.", "creationdate": "2020-10-14T18:33:26-05:00", "id": 1396641, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2556969, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "ThadTank", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 9, "id": 2578134, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "tankspank1", "body": "I don't know why everyone gives Xe'ra grief.  All she was doing was replacing Illidan's fel magic with the Light, not brainwashing him (note how the Lightforged Dreadlord Lothraxion was able to talk Xe'ra out of killing Alleria for using the Void, something he couldn't have done if Xe'ra brainwashed him, and if she was really that bad she would've killed Alleria anyway).  She's been fighting the Legion for millennia and predates even the Titans; Blizzard could've done so much more with this character but instead they wasted her on some \"Is the Light good or maybe not?\" story arc.  Besides, Illidan did worse to Akama (look up Shade of Akama on wowpedia).  Essentially, Illidan wasn't honoring his deal with Akama, locked him out of the loop and started acting more and more like an actual member of the Burning Legion, so Akama turned on him; in response Illidan enslaved a part of Akama's soul and threatened to have it devour him if he didn't do what Illidan said.  \r\n\r\nXe'ra's only mistake was not saying to Illidan \"I'm turning you into a form that Tyrande would want to bang\"; then he'd be all \"Let's do this!\"  (and also not telling the Army of the Light that Naaru could go Void).  So while Xe'ra has some problems, most of it is due to poor writing and comparing her to the Void or the Burning Legion is at best a knee-jerk reaction, at worst it says more about the people leveling the accusations than her.", "date": "2018-07-03T07:46:07-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Religion in any extreme is more evil than anything Illidan or Sylvanas could ever do. The Xe'ra of our reality is dead, Light be praised. But... She (Xe'ra) has now come complete circle and betrayed not only Yrel and the people of the au Draenor but the principles of the Light which say nothing about force proselytizing anyone. Yrel has her visions and marching orders from her Xe'ra - force proselytize the Great Beyond.", "creationdate": "2019-01-08T04:09:19-06:00", "id": 1214471, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2578134, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Dromboarstag", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I disagree. For one, how do you define when religion goes \"extreme\"? The fact remains that main timeline Xe'ra's actions fall short of Illidan's and your claim that Xe'ra's actions are \"...more evil than anything Sylvanas could ever do\" did not age well given the Burning of Teldrassil and her plans with the Jailer; Sylvanas and the Jailer are planning to break the cosmological machine of death and kill as many as they can. Let's say the Light wins and rules the Warcraft cosmos; while there's questions to be asked regarding the unwilling, what's wrong with a Light-ruled cosmos?", "creationdate": "2020-10-14T18:30:40-05:00", "id": 1396640, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2578134, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "ThadTank", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}